4. Bootstrap Integration 

 

Header
Footer
4

Bootstrap 5 is integrated to ensure a responsive and mobile-friendly layout. The CDN is used for both the Bootstrap CSS and JavaScript components. 

 

 

5. User Input Form 

 

  • A form allows users to enter their names. 

  • Bootstrap classes are used for styling, including form control and buttons. 

  • The "AddUser" button triggers the addition of a user to the to-do list. 

    •  

     

    6. Dynamic Table 

     

  • A dynamic table is implemented using Bootstrap's table classes. 

  • Columns include "Mark," "First," and "Action." 

  • User data is inserted dynamically into the table. 

    •  

     

     

    Header
    Footer
    5

     

    7. JavaScript Functionality 

     

  • External JavaScript (javascript.js) is linked to handle dynamic functionality. 

  • JavaScript functions manage user interactions, such as adding users to the list in real-time. 

    •  

     

    8. Conclusion 

     

    The To-Do List web app combines HTML, CSS, and JavaScript technologies to create an interactive and visually appealing user interface. Users can easily manage their to-do lists through a responsive and dynamic application.
